to teach you guys how to do it.

00:10:26.246 --> 00:10:28.698
But the important part is
after shuffling the cards,

00:10:28.698 --> 00:10:30.951
always remember
to cut and complete the cards.

00:10:30.951 --> 00:10:32.663
Do you mind doing that for me, sir?

00:10:32.663 --> 00:10:33.859
Please cut and complete.

00:10:33.859 --> 00:10:36.521
And when you have it,
place the cards up in the air.

00:10:36.521 --> 00:10:38.760
And you too, cut and complete
and up in the air.

00:10:38.784 --> 00:10:40.025
Up in the air.

00:10:40.025 --> 00:10:44.403
A deck of cards cut and shuffled
by one, two, three, four and five people.

00:10:44.403 --> 00:10:48.964
Now, very clearly, I'm going
to gather the deck together.

00:10:50.494 --> 00:10:53.233
And just like that.

00:10:54.163 --> 00:11:00.345
I'm going to search for a coincidence
in front of everyone.

00:11:03.955 --> 00:11:05.478
I'm going to try.

00:11:13.490 --> 00:11:17.689
I have some cards that maybe,

00:11:17.689 --> 00:11:19.972
maybe they don't mean anything.

00:11:20.904 --> 00:11:23.675
But maybe that's because
we are not paying close attention.

00:11:24.734 --> 00:11:28.317
Because maybe, maybe they mean a lot.

00:11:28.317 --> 00:11:31.766
Before we start,
sir, you gave me a dollar bill.

00:11:31.766 --> 00:11:33.649
Is that your signature?

00:11:33.649 --> 00:11:35.069
Audience member 3: Yes it is.

00:11:35.069 --> 00:11:39.174
HG: I want you to see very clearly

00:11:39.174 --> 00:11:42.431
that I'm going to open your bill

00:11:42.431 --> 00:11:47.228
and reveal a small secret that we created.

00:11:47.228 --> 00:11:53.357
And the secret of this dollar bill
is the serial number.

00:11:53.357 --> 00:11:56.280
Madam, can you take the dollar bill?

00:11:57.296 --> 00:11:59.242
In the serial number, there is a letter.

00:11:59.242 --> 00:12:02.485
